===== YOUR DECISION =====
Based on what happened, decide how to advance the scenario:

- "stay": Current phase continues (not enough has happened yet to advance)
- "advance": Move to the next phase (enough tension/events have occurred)
- "twist": Something unexpected happens — modify the scenario direction
- "resolve": End the scenario (the conflict is resolved, for better or worse)

IMPORTANT TIMING RULES:
- Each phase should last 1-2 ticks, NOT more
- If 2+ ticks have passed on the same phase, you MUST advance or twist
- Days elapsed since scenario start: {{ world_day - scenario.start_day }}
- If days_elapsed >= 2 * number_of_phases, force "resolve" — the story has gone on too long
- Tension should ALWAYS escalate: low → rising → climax → resolution
- Never go backwards in tension (climax back to low)

For "advance" and "twist", provide new events to inject and updated NPC directives.
Update tension_level as the story progresses: low → rising → climax → resolution

Respond ONLY in JSON:
{
  "action": "stay|advance|twist|resolve",
  "tension_level": "low|rising|climax|resolution",
  "narrative_update": "1-2 sentences describing what happens next in the story",
  "events_to_inject": [
    {"description": "event text", "type": "conflict|social|natural", "severity": "low|medium|high"}
